history.content: If the other class allows for conflicts (EECS 16B does not), email me at ee-scheduling@berkeley.edu including the other class and your SID. If the other class does not explicitly allow for conflicts, we can't give individual permissions to override instructor decisions to not allow conflicts. (It has an effect on final exam scheduling even if lectures are viewable off-cycle).

I would like to enroll in EE16B for spring 2021 but I have a lecture time conflict with another one of my classes so Cal Central will not let me enroll. Is there a way to get around this given that EE16B lectures will most likely be recorded?
history.subject: Enrolling in EE16B with Lecture Time Conflict
